HIV/Aids: China ta sanar da karuwar sabbin masu cutar da kashi 14%
Kasar Sin ta sanar da karuwar kashi 14% na yawan 'yan kasarta da ke dauke da cutar HIV da Aids.
Jami'an kiwon lafiya sun ce mutane fiye da 820,000 ne ke fama da cutar.
An gano kusan sabbin shari'o'i 40,000 a cikin kwata na biyu na 2018 kadai.
Yawancin lokuta ana samun su ta hanyar jima'i, suna nuna canji daga baya.
A al'adance, cutar HIV tana yaduwa cikin sauri ta wasu sassan kasar Sin sakamakon wadatar jini mai cutarwa.
Amma adadin mutanen da ke kamuwa da cutar HIV a wannan hanyar ya ragu kusan babu komai, in ji jami'an lafiya na kasar Sin a wani taro a lardin Yunnan.
Amma, a kowace shekara, yawan mutanen da ke da cutar kanjamau a kasar Sin ya karu da mutane 100,000.
Yaduwar HIV ta hanyar jima'i babbar matsala ce a cikin al'ummar LGBTI ta kasar Sin.
An yanke hukuncin kisa a kan luwadi a 1997, amma ana zargin nuna bambanci ga LGBT mutane yana da wahala.
Saboda dabi'un kasar, binciken ya nuna cewa kashi 70 zuwa 90 cikin dari na maza masu yin jima'i da maza za su auri mace.
Yawancin kamuwa da cuta suna faruwa ne saboda rashin lafiyar jima'i a cikin waɗannan alaƙar.
Tun daga 2003, gwamnatin kasar Sin ta yi alkawarin samar da maganin cutar HIV ga kowa a kasar a matsayin wani bangare na shirin magance matsalar.
